Package cpsc2150.extendedConnectX.models

Class GameBoardMem

  • java.lang.Object
    • cpsc2150.extendedConnectX.models.AbsGameBoard
      • cpsc2150.extendedConnectX.models.GameBoardMem
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IGameBoard
    public class GameBoardMem
extends AbsGameBoard
implements IGameBoard
    This class determines what characters are at certain positions and places tokens into the board using a map for memory efficiency.
    Invariant:
    0 <= row < MAX_NUM_ROWS AND 0 <= column <= MAX_NUM_COLUMNS, No tokens can be placed in a full column, No tokens can be placed outside of the board, No gaps between non-space positions
    Correspondence:
    minRow <= ROW <= maxRow, minColumn <= COLUMN <= maxColumn, minWin <= WIN <= maxWin, self = Map> board
    Section:
    CPSC 2151 007

    • Constructor Detail

      • GameBoardMem

        public GameBoardMem​(int r,
                    int c,
                    int w)
        The key field of our Map will be a Character that represents the player so that each player will get their own entry in the Map. The value associated with that player will be a List of BoardPositions that the player occupies on the board. If a player has not placed a token yet, then there will be no key or List in the Map to represent that player.
        Parameters:
        r - The number of rows the board will have
        c - The number of columns the board will have
        w - The number of tokens in a row needed to win
        Post:
        [board map is created with key value pair of characters and lists of BoardPositions] AND ROW = r, COLUMN = c, WIN = w
